<subSubSection id="6B60CD92569B76156EA51092AB8C8A9C" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F471CFA3B2A0597ECC9212B7BD516CB7" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D7E931C62F09895D5A552FF3BC271BC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
This species differs from other Palaearctic species of the genus by having forewings with two submarginal cells (versus three cells in other species, except 
<taxonomicName id="C2FA9DAA054E95564576360C3FE22FB4" family="Apidae" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. bischoffi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="bischoffi">
<emphasis id="3C17D355452176EB755B3DE244D3F107" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">E. bischoffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mavromoustakis, 1954) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9F76ADA5E80F0DE7BA11154411ED578C" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Epeolus leleji sp. nov., holotype, male A, B habitus, lateral view (A); dorsal view (B). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.67150.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578840" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">2A, B</figureCitation>
). The new species are clearly distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="A368C75FBCCA7DC4E4E5A245AD35D07D" family="Apidae" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. bischoffi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="bischoffi">
<emphasis id="C7A483270FFD3F919289A21FF0964ADC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">E. bischoffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by lack of long black dense hair on the whole body, position of labral teeth closer to apical margin, the reddish female mesosoma (black in 
<taxonomicName id="56820DE3C2D9DC8D4CABFC10C3DB2740" family="Apidae" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. bischoffi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="bischoffi">
<emphasis id="D002E10DA00FC89755217878965799BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">E. bischoffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and many other characters.
</paragraph>
<caption id="A511FF18C70B6E94128B5053CF74BBF1" doi="10.3897/jhr.84.67150.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578840" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="A7C180BFA301C45D4A9D1268C5C19E04" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
